</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="71" type="mainText">
Note: Section Mitellaria, including only 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pentandra">M. pentandra</taxonomicName>
of North America, is similar to sect. 
<taxonomicName authority="R.A.Folk &amp; Y.Okuyama (Wakab.)" authorityName="R.A.Folk &amp; Y.Okuyama (Wakab.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Asimitellaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Asimitellaria">Asimitellaria</taxonomicName>
in having five stamens opposite the petals, but distinctly differs in having glabrous, smooth, black seeds, and a chromosome count of 2n = 14. Section 
<taxonomicName authority="R.A.Folk &amp; Y.Okuyama (Wakab.)" authorityName="R.A.Folk &amp; Y.Okuyama (Wakab.)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Asimitellaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Asimitellaria">Asimitellaria</taxonomicName>
has 2n = 28 showing diploidized allotetraploidy. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosana">M. formosana</taxonomicName>
of Taiwan also belongs to this section. The sections, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Mitella</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diphylla">M. diphylla</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Howell" authorityName="Howell" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitellastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Mitellastra">Mitellastra</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Howell" authorityName="Howell" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitellastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caulescens">M. caulescens</taxonomicName>
), Mitellina (
<taxonomicName authority="Howell" authorityName="Howell" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitellastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stauropetala">M. stauropetala</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="," authorityName="," class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitellastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="trifida">
M. trifida
<authority>,</authority>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName genus="Mitellinae" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" rank="species" species="diversifolia">M. diversifolia</taxonomicName>
), Brewerimitella (M. breweri, 
<taxonomicName authority="Howell" authorityName="Howell" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Mitellastra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="1" pageNumber="71" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ovalis">M. ovalis</taxonomicName>
), are in North America.
</paragraph>
